President Donald Trump has nominated David Reimer as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Sierra Leone. Reimer is a Career Member of the Senior Foreign Service and holds the position of Counselor. Additionally, Eric J. Soskin has been nominated to be the Inspector General of the Department of Transportation, replacing Calvin L. Scovel who resigned. Soskin is from Virginia. These nominations have been sent to the Senate for consideration.